statements: SELECT * FROM trading_log;
SELECT signal_id, signal_datetime, signal_type FROM trading_log ORDER BY signal_datetime DESC;
SELECT * FROM trading_log WHERE signal_type = 'Buy';
SELECT signal_id, algorithm_used, effectiveness FROM trading_log WHERE signal_type = 'Sell';
SELECT * FROM trading_log ORDER BY effectiveness DESC LIMIT 3;
SELECT * FROM trading_log WHERE signal_type = 'Buy' AND effectiveness > 0.8 ORDER BY signal_datetime DESC LIMIT 10;
SELECT signal_id, signal_datetime, action_taken FROM trading_log WHERE algorithm_used = 'Trend Following' ORDER BY signal_id ASC;
SELECT signal_id, signal_datetime, signal_type FROM trading_log WHERE action_taken = 'execute' AND effectiveness >= 0.9 ORDER BY signal_type ASC, signal_datetime DESC;
SELECT signal_id, algorithm_used, effectiveness FROM trading_log WHERE signal_type = 'Sell' AND action_taken = 'sell' ORDER BY effectiveness DESC, signal_id ASC;
SELECT * FROM trading_log WHERE signal_datetime BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-03-31' AND signal_type IN ('Buy', 'Sell') ORDER BY signal_datetime DESC, signal_type ASC LIMIT 5;

SELECT symbol, signal_type FROM trading_signals ORDER BY timestamp DESC;
SELECT * FROM trading_actions WHERE quantity > 100 ORDER BY timestamp ASC;
SELECT symbol, confidence_score FROM trading_signals WHERE confidence_score > 0.8;
SELECT DISTINCT symbol FROM trading_actions ORDER BY symbol ASC;

SELECT symbol, COUNT(*) AS signal_count FROM trading_signals GROUP BY symbol HAVING COUNT(*) > 10;
SELECT symbol, MAX(confidence_score) AS max_confidence FROM trading_signals WHERE timestamp >= '2022-01-01' GROUP BY symbol;
SELECT symbol, action_type, timestamp FROM trading_actions WHERE quantity > 100 ORDER BY timestamp ASC LIMIT 10;
SELECT symbol, signal_type, timestamp FROM trading_signals UNION SELECT symbol, action_type, timestamp FROM trading_actions ORDER BY timestamp DESC;
